     src: url("//fonts.gstatic.com/s/roboto/v18/hNdh1kLam5Qu9t6-swGJgPesZW2xOQ-xsNqO47m55DA.eot?#iefix");

             <div class="txtNew" data-min-height="557" data-packed="false" id="comp-j4gsnic4" style="top:1869px;bottom:;left:6px;right:;width:492px;height:auto;position:absolute;min-height:557px;margin-left:calc((100% - 980px) * 0.5)">
              <h6 class="font_6" style="text-align:center;">
               <span style="color:#000000;">
                "The Plan of God - Work It Out" - Pastor Kemi (G.O.)
               </span>
              </h6>
              <p class="font_8" style="text-align:center;">
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                The thoughts and plans of God for the children of Israel was for them to
               </span>
               <span style="font-size:15px; font-weight:bold;">
                buildhouses
               </span>
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                and
               </span>
               <span style="font-size:15px; font-weight:bold;">
                plantgardens
               </span>
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                (
               </span>
               <span style="font-size:15px; font-weight:bold;">
                Jeremiah 29:4-8, 11-13
               </span>
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                ). Thatword was sent to
               </span>
               <span style="font-size:15px; font-weight:bold;">
                all
               </span>
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                of them, but not all followed the word, even thoughthat was the plan of God for them. Somewhere along the line, the plan of God failed for them, either becausethey did not receive the word as for them, or because they didn't feel they could achieve it.
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="text-align:center;">
               <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                <span style="font-style:italic;">
                 <span style="font-size:15px;">
                  God has a plan for your life, but that does not mean that you yourself will follow the plan.
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="text-align:center;">
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                <span class="wixGuard">
                 
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="text-align:center;">
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                God made His thoughts and plans for Israel plain and clear; theyneeded no interpretation. He even gave them the clue to enjoying those plans; simply tocallon Him and seekHim (
                <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                 Jeremiah 29:11-12
                </span>
                ).
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="text-align:center;">
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                <span class="wixGuard">
                 
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="text-align:center;">
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                God's plan for our life is the
                <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                 reason
                </span>
                and
                <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                 purpose
                </span>
                for our existence. He has a plan for
                <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                 everyone
                </span>
                that is born. On top of that, we have plans for our own life, our family and friends may also have plans for us.
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="text-align:center;">
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                <span class="wixGuard">
                 
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="text-align:center;">
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                There is a
               </span>
               <span style="font-size:15px; font-weight:bold;">
                master-planof God
               </span>
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                for everyone who is born no matter who they are or where they were born. Whatever God says we should do, that is His plan for us; a plan which we have allbroken at some point in our lives(
               </span>
               <span style="font-size:15px; font-weight:bold;">
                Exodus 20
               </span>
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                ).
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="text-align:center;">
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="text-align:center;">
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                On top of that, His master-plan for us is to
                <span style="text-decoration:underline;">
                 love Him and serve Him
                </span>
                with all our heart and soul (
                <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                 Deuteronomy 6:5; 10:12-13, 20-21; 11:13-15, 22-25;1 Samuel 12:24
                </span>
                ).
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="text-align:center;">
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                <span class="wixGuard">
                 
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="text-align:center;">
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                The
               </span>
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                 primary love of God
                </span>
               </span>
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                should supersedeevery other layer of love you have for people. If you don't love people, the master-plan of God cannot be working in your life.
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="text-align:center;">
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                <span class="wixGuard">
                 
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="text-align:center;">
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                The master-plan of God should shape the plans you have for your own life. If not, your plans will be contrary to God's plan for your life.
                <span style="font-style:italic;">
                 <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                  Become the master-plan, meditate on it, carry it all around with you.
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="text-align:center;">
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="text-align:center;">
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                Once your life has been shaped by the master-plan of God, His
                <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                 specific plan
                </span>
                will follow. You will also be able to discern between your plans and His plans.
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="text-align:center;">
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                Jacob, Joseph, David, Solomon, and Jeremiah all had specific plans of God operating in their lives (
                <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                 Genesis 25:21-23, 37:6-11; 1 Samuel 16:1; 2 Samuel 7:12-15, 12:24-25; Jeremiah 1:4-5
                </span>
                ).
               </span>
              </p>
             </div>
             <style data-styleid="txtNew" type="text/css">
              .txtNew {word-wrap:break-word;text-align:start;pointer-events:none;}

 .txtNew ul ul,.txtNew ol ul {list-style-type:circle;}

             <div class="txtNew" data-min-height="48" data-packed="false" id="comp-iozln1ib" style="top:1870px;bottom:;left:508px;right:;width:467px;height:auto;position:absolute;min-height:48px;margin-left:calc((100% - 980px) * 0.5)">
              <h6 class="font_6" style="text-align:center;">
               <span style="color:#000000;">
                "Knowing God Personally &amp; Passionately - How It Works" - Pastor Kemi (G.O.)
               </span>
              </h6>
              <p class="font_8" style="text-align:center;">
               <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size:15px;">
                Knowing God personally and passionately means
                <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                 relationship plus fellowship
                </span>
                . It is possible to come to Church and call yourself a child of God by relationship whilethere is no fellowship with Him behind that relationship. Singing, serving andministering the word can all be done by those who have no fellowship with Him.
                <span style="text-decoration:underline;">
                 So what, then, is the test to discern those who are connected to God by relationship and fellowship and those who are not?
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="text-align:center;">
               <span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size:15px;">
                <span class="wixGuard">
                 
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:15px; text-align:center;">
               <span style="color:#000000;">
                <span style="font-size:15px;">
                 <span style="font-style:italic;">
                  Hear, O Israel:TheLordour God, theLordisone!You shall love theLordyour God with all your heart,with all your soul, and with all your strength.
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
               <span style="color:#000000;">
                <span style="font-size:15px;">
                 <span style="font-style:italic;">
                  
                 </span>
                 (
                 <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                  Deuteronomy 6:4-5
                 </span>
                 )
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:15px; text-align:center;">
               <span style="color:#000000;">
                <span style="font-size:15px;">
                 <span class="wixGuard">
                  
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:15px; text-align:center;">
               <span style="color:#000000;">
                <span style="font-size:15px;">
                 It is impossible to know God and not love Him. Those who truly know Him and are in fellowship with Him will
                 <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                  love Him
                 </span>
                 and everything they do will be outof that love and not for selfish ambitions. Those who know Him and love Him will
                 <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                  cling to Him
                 </span>
                 in every situation they face in life - they will have a
                 <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                  clinging love
                 </span>
                 for Him (
                 <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                  Deuteronomy 10:20; 2 Kings 2:1-6
                 </span>
                 ).
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:15px; text-align:center;">
               <span style="color:#000000;">
                <span style="font-size:15px;">
                 <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                  <span style="text-decoration:underline;">
                   <span class="wixGuard">
                    
                   </span>
                  </span>
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:15px; text-align:center;">
               <span style="color:#000000;">
                <span style="text-decoration:underline;">
                 <span style="font-size:15px;">
                  There are
                  <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                   5 areas
                  </span>
                  of your life that knowing Him personally and passionately
                  <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                   will work for you
                  </span>
                  :
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:15px; text-align:center;">
               <span style="color:#000000;">
                <span style="font-size:15px;">
                 <span class="wixGuard">
                  
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:15px; text-align:center;">
               <span style="color:#000000;">
                <span style="font-size:15px;">
                 1) It secures the
                 <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                  promises of God
                 </span>
                 for your life (
                 <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                  Joshua 21:45
                 </span>
                 )
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:15px; text-align:center;">
               <span style="color:#000000;">
                <span style="font-size:15px;">
                 <span class="wixGuard">
                  
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:15px; text-align:center;">
               <span style="color:#000000;">
                <span style="font-size:15px;">
                 2) It will bring you
                 <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                  helpers
                 </span>
                 in every part of your journey - you will never walk alone, even when the night is at it's darkest (
                 <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                  1 Chronicles 12:1
                 </span>
                 ).
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:15px; text-align:center;">
               <span style="color:#000000;">
                <span style="font-size:15px;">
                 <span class="wixGuard">
                  
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:15px; text-align:center;">
               <span style="color:#000000;">
                <span style="font-size:15px;">
                 3) It will lead you to
                 <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                  the places that God has planned out for you
                 </span>
                 despite anything pushing and shoving you in the wrong direction (
                 <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                  1 Samuel 23:5-14
                 </span>
                 ).
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:15px; text-align:center;">
               <span style="color:#000000;">
                <span style="font-size:15px;">
                 <span class="wixGuard">
                  
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:15px; text-align:center;">
               <span style="color:#000000;">
                <span style="font-size:15px;">
                 4) It will bring you
                 <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                  prosperity in times of adversity
                 </span>
                 - God always uses adversity to bring you to a place of prosperity if you are where He wants you to be, doing what He wants you to do (
                 <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                  1 Samuel 30
                 </span>
                 ).
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:15px; text-align:center;">
               <span style="color:#000000;">
                <span style="font-size:15px;">
                 <span class="wixGuard">
                  
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:15px; text-align:center;">
               <span style="color:#000000;">
                <span style="font-size:15px;">
                 5) It will
                 <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                  strengthen you
                 </span>
                 when you are faced with the challenges of life - when enemies rise up against you, God will intervene on your behalf (
                 <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                  Numbers 12;16:1-5, 20-27
                 </span>
                 ).
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
             </div>

               <span style="font-size:20px;">
                <span class="color_16">
                 <span style="font-family:arial;">

                   KNOWING GOD PERSONALLY &amp; PASSIONATELY -
                  </span>
                 </span>

               <span style="font-size:20px;">
                <span class="color_16">
                 <span style="font-family:arial;">

                   JOHN 17:3
                  </span>
                 </span>

             <style data-styleid="txtNew" type="text/css">
              .txtNew {word-wrap:break-word;text-align:start;pointer-events:none;}
 .txtNew_override-left * {text-align:left !important;}
 .txtNew_override-right * {text-align:right !important;}
